{"id":"v053","internalId":"f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09","createdAt":"2026-02-12T09:44:44.241Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-28T16:02:33.850Z","status":{"code":"PUBLISHED","name":"Published"},"assessmentType":{"code":"VAN_SAFETY","name":"Van Safety"},"assessmentDiagrams":[],"publicationDate":"2025-05-01","publicationYear":"2025","ratingYear":2025,"SPRefNumber":"v053","umbracoRefNumber":null,"rescueSheetURL":null,"greenNcapURL":null,"frontalImageURL":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__07c0ea21a7b52e4d_original.png","frontalImage":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__07c0ea21a7b52e4d_original.png","altText":null,"width":1144,"height":760,"formats":{"large":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__24712749064ab481_lg.webp","width":1144,"height":760},"small":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__685c8cae922f6bbd_sm.webp","width":320,"height":213},"medium":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__8d9439b8688eaa02_md.webp","width":768,"height":510},"xlarge":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__24712749064ab481_xl.webp","width":1144,"height":760},"thumbnail":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/f2204388-635c-4511-807b-d338ca42da09/citroen-berlingo-2025-v083__d526885920eb6800_thumb.webp","width":156,"height":104}}},"newsMarketURL":"https://news.euroncap.com/safertrucksandvans/choose-a-vehicle/citro-n-berlingo---euro-ncap-2025-commercial-van-safety---4-stars/s/fe23515c-fe62-41b4-863c-f5dc03631553","resultApplicability":"all Berlingos, 3rd generation, K9, from 2018","comments":"<p>The Citroën Berlingo comes with a variety of powertrains. The van tested here is the ë-Berlingo electric version but the rating applies more broadly. <p><p>The safety systems show limited performance compared with competitors in this segment and the Berlingo offers a four-star level of safety. The autonomous emergency braking (AEB) system uses camera-based technology to detect other vehicles and vulnerable road users such as pedestrians and cyclists. Performance is good when approaching a stationary or slower-moving car at lower speeds, but deteriorates as test speeds increase. However, performance is symmetrical, reacting equally well to a target vehicle is straight in front of it or offset to one side or the other. Unlike some of its competitors, the Berlingo does not react to a vehicle which turns across its path. With a pedestrian target, the system performs well or adequately in the simpler scenarios, with some drop-off when tested in night-time conditions, but does not intervene if a pedestrian is behind the van as it reverses or when the van turns into the path of a crossing pedestrian. In Euro NCAP’s tests, the Berlingo showed very little reaction to a cyclist. <p><p>The lane support system includes lane departure warning, which signals to the driver when the van is drifting out of lane, and emergency lane keeping, which intervenes more aggressively in certain critical situations to prevent the van from leaving the road. The system performed well in all tests, but does not include blind spot monitoring. <p><p>The Berlingo uses a camera to identify the local speed limit and provides the information to the driver, allowing the limiter to be set accordingly. The limiter is able to maintain the set speed to within 5&nbsp;km/h. <p><p>A seatbelt reminder is standard for the driver and front passenger seat, and the Berlingo recognises steering behaviour which is characteristic of fatigued driving, alerting the driver to the need for a break. <p><p>Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC) has not been assessed as part of the current rating. <p>","testedHandOfDrive":null,"assessmentTags":[],"assessmentData":{"vanSafety":{"testedModelName":"Citroën ë-Berlingo","nicePublicationDate":"May 2025","safetyPerformance":{"starRating":4,"safeDriving":{"normalisedScore":73,"occupantMonitoring":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"seatbeltUsage":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN"}},"driverEngagement":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"driverMonitoring":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN"}},"vehicleAssistance":{"score":23,"maxScore":50,"speedAssistance":{"score":23,"maxScore":30,"verdict":"GREEN"},"adaptiveCruiseControl":{"score":0,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"GREY"},"steeringAssistance":{"score":0,"maxScore":5,"verdict":"GREY"}}},"crashAvoidance":{"normalisedScore":47,"frontalCollisions":{"score":25.1,"maxScore":65,"car":{"score":17.6,"maxScore":40,"verdict":"ORANGE"},"pedestrianAndCyclist":{"score":7.5,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"ORANGE"}},"laneDepartureCollisions":{"score":21.7,"maxScore":25,"laneDeparture":{"score":15,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"GREEN"},"car":{"score":6.7,"maxScore":10,"verdict":"YELLOW"}},"lowSpeedCollisions":{"score":0,"maxScore":10,"pedestrian":{"score":0,"maxScore":10,"verdict":"GREY"}}},"postCrashSafety":{"normalisedScore":80,"rescueInformation":{"score":80,"maxScore":90,"rescueSheet":{"score":80,"maxScore":90,"verdict":"GREEN"}},"postCrashIntervention":{"score":0,"maxScore":5,"advancedECall":{"score":0,"maxScore":5,"verdict":"GREY"}},"vehicleExtrication":{"score":0,"maxScore":5,"occupantExtrication":{"score":0,"maxScore":5,"verdict":"GREY"}}}},"safetyEquipment":{"safeDriving":{"seatBeltReminderDriver":"FITTED_STANDARD","seatBeltReminderPassenger":"FITTED_STANDARD","driverMonitoring":"OPTIONAL","speedAssistance":"FITTED_STANDARD","adaptiveCruiseControl":"FITTED_STANDARD","steeringAssistance":"NOT_AVAILABLE"},"crashAvoidance":{"carAEB":"FITTED_STANDARD","pedestrianAndCyclistAEB":"FITTED_STANDARD","